#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:16
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:99
msgid "Lighten"
msgstr "相対明色"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:18
msgid "Blending modes that lighten the image."
msgstr "画像を明るくする合成モードです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:20
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:24
msgid "Color Dodge"
msgstr "覆い焼き(色)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:20
msgid "Dodge"
msgstr "覆い焼き"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:28
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Color Dodge\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:30
msgid ""
"Similar to Divide. Inverts the top layer, and divides the lower layer by the "
"inverted top layer. This results in a image with emphasized highlights, like "
"Dodging would do in traditional darkroom photography."
msgstr ""
"除算に似ています。上のレイヤーを反転し、下のレイヤーを反転させた上のレイヤー"
"で割り算します。結果は暗室の写真で覆い焼きするように、ハイライトを強調した画"
"像になります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:37
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Color_Dodge_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:37
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Color Dodge**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **覆い焼き(色)**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:39
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:43
msgid "Gamma Illumination"
msgstr "ガンマライト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:47
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Gamma Illumination\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:49
msgid "Inverted Gamma Dark blending mode."
msgstr "ガンマダーク合成モードを反転させたものです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:54
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Gamma_Illumination_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:54
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Gamma Illumination**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **ガンマライト**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:57
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:61
msgid "Gamma Light"
msgstr "ガンマライト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:65
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Gamma Light\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:67
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Outputs the upper layer as power of the lower layer."
msgid "Outputs the upper layer as a power of the lower layer."
msgstr "上のレイヤーを下のレイヤーの指数として出力します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:72
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Gamma_Light_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:72
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Gamma Light**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **ガンマライト**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:74
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:78
msgid "Hard Light"
msgstr "ハードライト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:82
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Hard Light\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:84
msgid ""
"Similar to Overlay. A combination of the Multiply and Screen blending modes, "
"switching between both at a middle-lightness."
msgstr ""
"オーバーレイに似ています。乗算とスクリーン合成モードが合体したもので、中間明"
"度でその二つを切り替えます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:87
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Hard light checks if the color on the upperlayer has a lightness above "
#| "0.5. Unlike overlay, if the pixel is lighter than 0.5, it is blended like "
#| "in Multiply mode, if not the pixel is blended like in Screen mode."
msgid ""
"Hard Light checks if the color on the upper layer has a lightness above 0.5. "
"Unlike Overlay, if the pixel is lighter than 0.5, it is blended like in "
"Multiply mode, if not the pixel is blended like in Screen mode."
msgstr ""
"ハードライトは上側レイヤー色の明るさが0.5を超えているか確認します。オーバーレ"
"イとは違い、ピクセルの明るさが0.5を超えていれば乗算のように合成され、出なけれ"
"ばスクリーンモードのように合成されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:89
msgid "Effectively, this decreases contrast."
msgstr "これにより効果的にコントラストが抑えられます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:94
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Hard_Light_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:94
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Hard Light**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **ハードライト**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:103
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Lighten\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:105
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "With the darken, the upper layer's colors are checked for their "
#| "lightness. Only if they are Lighter than the underlying color on the "
#| "lower layer, will they be visible."
msgid ""
"With Lighten, the upper layer's colors are checked for their lightness. Only "
"if they are Lighter than the underlying color on the lower layer, will they "
"be visible."
msgstr ""
"色を暗くするでは、上側レイヤー色の明度が確認されます。下にあるレイヤーの色よ"
"り明るい場合だけ、表示されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:110
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Lighten_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:110
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Lighten**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **相対明色**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:115
msgid "Lighter Color"
msgstr "明度を上げる"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:119
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Lighter Color\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:124
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Lighter_Color_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:124
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Lighter Color**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **明度を上げる**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:130
msgid "Linear Dodge"
msgstr "覆い焼き(線形)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:134
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Linear Dodge\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:136
msgid "Exactly the same as :ref:`bm_addition`."
msgstr ":ref:`bm_addition` と全く同じです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:138
msgid "Put in for compatibility purposes."
msgstr "互換性維持のために置いてあります。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:143
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Linear_Dodge_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:143
msgid ""
"Left: **Normal**. Right: **Linear Dodge** (exactly the same as Addition)."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **覆い焼き(線形)** (加算と全く同じ)."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:148
msgid "Easy Dodge"
msgstr "覆い焼き"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:152
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Easy Dodge\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:154
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Aims to solve issues with Color Dodge blending mode by using a formula "
#| "which falloff is similar to Dodge, but the falloff rate is softer. It is "
#| "within the range of 0.0f and 1.0f unlike Color Dodge mode."
msgid ""
"Aims to solve issues with Color Dodge blending mode by using a formula in "
"which falloff is similar to Dodge, but the falloff rate is softer. It is "
"within the range of 0.0f and 1.0f unlike Color Dodge mode."
msgstr ""
"覆い焼き(色)合成モードの問題を焼き込みに似た減衰する数式を使うことで、しかし"
"減衰率を緩やかにすることによって解決しようとしました。覆い焼き(色)と違い0.0f"
"から1.0fの範囲で表されます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:159
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Easy_Dodge_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:159
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Easy Dodge**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **覆い焼き**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:164
msgid "Flat Light"
msgstr "フラットライト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:168
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Flat Light\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:170
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The spreadout variation of Vivid Light mode which range is between 0.0f "
#| "and 1.0f."
msgid ""
"The spreadout variation of Vivid Light mode in which range is between 0.0f "
"and 1.0f."
msgstr "範囲0.0fから1.0fの、ビビッドライトモードの派生です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:175
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Flat_Light_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:175
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Flat Light**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **フラットライト**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:180
msgid "Fog Lighten (IFS Illusions)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:184
msgid ""
"This blending mode is called \"Fog Lighten (IFS Illusions)\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:186
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Lightens the image in a way that there is a 'fog' in the end result. This "
#| "is due to the unique property of fog lighten in which midtones combined "
#| "are lighter than non-midtones blend."
msgid ""
"Lightens the image in a way that there is a 'fog' in the end result. This is "
"due to the unique property of Fog Lighten in which midtones combined are "
"lighter than non-midtones blend."
msgstr ""
"結果に'霧'が残るように画像を明るくします。これは中間色の組み合わせがそうでな"
"いものより明るくなる fog lighten の特徴によるものです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:191
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Fog_Light_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:191
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Fog Lighten**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **Fog Lighten**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:196
msgid "Linear Light"
msgstr "リニアライト"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:200
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Linear Light\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:202
msgid "Similar to :ref:`bm_overlay`."
msgstr ":ref:`bm_overlay` と似ています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:204
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Combines :ref:`bm_linear_dodge` and :ref:`bm_linear_burn`. When the "
#| "lightness of the upper-pixel is higher than 0.5, it uses Linear dodge, if "
#| "not, Linear burn to blend the pixels."
msgid ""
"Combines :ref:`bm_linear_dodge` and :ref:`bm_linear_burn`. When the "
"lightness of the upper-pixel is higher than 0.5, it uses Linear Dodge, if "
"not, Linear Burn to blend the pixels."
msgstr ""
":ref:`bm_linear_dodge` と :ref:`bm_linear_burn` を組み合わせたものです。上側"
"ピクセルの明度が0.5を超える場合覆い焼き(線形)を使用し、そうでない時に焼き込み"
"(リニア)を使用してピクセルを合成します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:209
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Linear_Light_Gray_0.4_and_Gray_0.5.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:209
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:214
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:219
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Linear Light**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **リニアライト**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:214
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Linear_Light_Light_blue_and_Orange.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:219
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Linear_Light_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:225
msgid "Luminosity/Shine (SAI)"
msgstr "光度/輝度 (SAI)"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:229
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Luminosity/Shine (SAI)\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:231
msgid "Similar to :ref:`bm_addition`."
msgstr ":ref:`bm_addition` と似ています。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:233
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Takes the opacity of the new color (combined opacity of the layer, the "
#| "brush, any used transparency masks etc.) and multiples the color by the "
#| "opacity, then adds to the original/previous color."
msgid ""
"Takes the opacity of the new color (combined opacity of the layer, the "
"brush, any used transparency masks, etc.) and multiplies the color by the "
"opacity, then adds to the original/previous color."
msgstr ""
"新しい透過度を取り(レイヤーの透過度、ブラシ、他の透過マスクなど)、色を透過度"
"で乗算したうえで元の/前の色を加えます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:235
msgid "c_{new} = c_{above}*{\\alpha}_{above} + c_{below}"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:239
msgid ""
"The result of this operation is the same as combining the new pixels with a "
"fully opaque black layer in a :ref:`bm_normal` mode and then combining the "
"result with the original layer using :ref:`bm_addition` mode. It should be "
"also the same as the results of \"Luminosity\" blending mode in SAI1 or "
"\"Shine\" blending mode in SAI2."
msgstr ""
"この演算結果は :ref:`bm_normal` モードの完全に不透明な黒レイヤーを新しいピク"
"セルと組み合わせた後に、:ref:`bm_addition` モードを使って元レイヤーをさらに組"
"み合わせたものと同じです。SAI2の\"発光\"合成モードとほぼ同じです。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:246
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Luminosity_Shine_SAI_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:246
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Luminosity/Shine (SAI)**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **光度/輝度 (SAI)**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:254
msgid "P-Norm A"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:258
msgid "This blending mode is called \"P-Norm A\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:260
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "P-Norm A is similar to Screen blending mode which slightly darken images, "
#| "and the falloff is more consistent all-around in terms of outline of "
#| "values. Can be used an alternative to screen blending mode at times."
msgid ""
"P-Norm A is similar to Screen blending mode which slightly darken images, "
"and the falloff is more consistent all-around in terms of outline of values. "
"Can be used an alternative to Screen blending mode at times."
msgstr ""
"P-Norm A はわずかに画像を暗くするスクリーン合成モードと似ていて、値の輪郭とい"
"う点では減衰が全体的に維持し続けます。場合によってスクリーン合成モードの代替"
"として使用できます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:265
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/Blending_modes_P-"
"Norm_A_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:265
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **P-Norm A**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **P-Norm A**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:270
msgid "P-Norm B"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:274
msgid "This blending mode is called \"P-Norm B\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:276
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "P-Norm B is similar to Screen blending mode which slightly darken images, "
#| "and the falloff is more consistent all-around in terms of outline of "
#| "values. The falloff is sharper in P-Norm B than in P-Norm A. Can be used "
#| "an alternative to screen blending mode at times."
msgid ""
"P-Norm B is similar to Screen blending mode which slightly darken images, "
"and the falloff is more consistent all-around in terms of outline of values. "
"The falloff is sharper in P-Norm B than in P-Norm A. Can be used as an "
"alternative to Screen blending mode at times."
msgstr ""
"P-Norm B はわずかに画像を暗くするスクリーン合成モードと似ていて、値の輪郭とい"
"う点では減衰が全体的に維持し続けます。P-Norm B の減衰は P-Norm A のより鋭いで"
"す。場合によりスクリーン合成モードの代替として使えます。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:281
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/Blending_modes_P-"
"Norm_B_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:281
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **P-Norm B**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. 右: **P-Norm B**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:286
msgid "Pin Light"
msgstr "ライトをピン留めする"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:290
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Pin Light\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:292
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Checks which is darker the lower layer's pixel or the upper layer's "
#| "double so bright. Then checks which is brighter of that result or the "
#| "inversion of the doubled lower layer."
msgid ""
"Checks which is darker between the lower layer's pixel or the upper layer's "
"double so bright. Then checks which is brighter of that result or the "
"inversion of the doubled lower layer."
msgstr ""
"下のレイヤーか上のレイヤー明度の2倍のどちらが暗いかを確認します。それからその"
"結果と下のレイヤーの2倍を反転させたもののどちらが明るいかを確認します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:298
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Pin_Light_Gray_0.4_and_Gray_0.5.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:298
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:303
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:308
msgid "Left: **Normal**. Right: **Pin Light**."
msgstr "左: **通常**. Right: **ライトをピン留めする**."

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:303
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Pin_Light_Light_blue_and_Orange.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:308
msgid ""
".. image:: /images/blending_modes/lighten/"
"Blending_modes_Pin_Light_Sample_image_with_dots.png"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:313
msgid "Screen"
msgstr "スクリーン"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:317
msgid "This blending mode is called \"Screen\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:319
msgid "Perceptually the opposite of :ref:`bm_multiply`."
msgstr "視覚的に :ref:`bm_multiply` と反対です。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:321
msgid ""
"Mathematically, Screen takes both layers, inverts them, then multiplies "
"them, and finally inverts them again."
msgstr ""
"数学的にはスクリーンは両方のレイヤーを反転し、乗算し、最後にまた反転します。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:323
msgid ""
"This results in light tones being more opaque and dark tones transparent."
msgstr "これによって暗色は透明に、明色はより不透明になります。"

