"These blending modes are called \"Soft Light (Photoshop)\" and \"Soft Light "
"SVG\" in English."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:349
msgid ""
"These are less harsh versions of Hard Light, not resulting in full black or "
"full white."
msgstr "ハードライトより尖りのないもので、全くの黒や白になりません。"

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../reference_manual/blending_modes/lighten.rst:351
msgid ""
"The SVG version is slightly different to the Photoshop version in that it "
"uses a slightly different bit of formula when the lightness of the lower "
"pixel is lower than 25%, this prevents the strength of the brightness "
"increase."
msgstr ""
"SVG の方は Photoshop にあるものとは少し異なっていて、ピクセルの明るさが25%を"
"下回ると輝度強さの上昇を抑えるちょっと違った数式を使っています。"

